put pattern.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[{"__typename":"Markup","type":"A","start":39,"end":49,"href":"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Frg3\u002Fyoutube-dl","anchorType":"LINK","userId":null,"linkMetadata":null}],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:8d7b84ec45f2_19":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"8d7b84ec45f2_19","name":"3052","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Another point is to clarify which tool\u002Flibrary should I use to compress the downloaded videos from Youtube. With help of a little bit googling, I found out that pigz is quite nice tool which compress given folder\u002Ffile in paralel by using all available cores of the machine. The second requirement is cleared as well, now it is time to combine both of them in one and add Github workflow on top it.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[{"__typename":"Markup","type":"CODE","start":161,"end":165,"href":null,"anchorType":null,"userId":null,"linkMetadata":null}],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:8d7b84ec45f2_20":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"8d7b84ec45f2_20","name":"e622","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"I will mention about the Github workflow file, after structure of the program which automates the process.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:8d7b84ec45f2_21":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"8d7b84ec45f2_21","name":"1128","type":"H3","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Code Structure","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:8d7b84ec45f2_22":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"8d7b84ec45f2_22","name":"15a0","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"To make things faster (- in terms of development time -), I decided to go with using pre-existing binary file to execute commands, what I mean by that is basically having a pre-installed tool (youtube-dl & pigz) on the system before using this application.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:8d7b84ec45f2_23":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"8d7b84ec45f2_23","name":"a706","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"If the readme file of youtube-dl is checked, youtube-dl can be installed as command line tool into your environment. It means that we can call the tool whenever we need from our application. There are other ways to accomblish it as well, such as instead of using pre-existing binary file, we can implement the functions in our application. However, the main idea of this post is NOT about how to create or use the library, the main idea is to present how it easy to have automated way of retrieving Youtube playlist videos and saving to Github Releases. The other requirement regarding to compress can be used in similar way. (- using a pre-existin command from system -)","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[{"__typename":"Markup","type":"A","start":22,"end":32,"href":"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fytdl-org\u002Fyoutube-dl","anchorType":"LINK","userId":null,"linkMetadata":null}],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:8d7b84ec45f2_24":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"8d7b84ec45f2_24","name":"20db","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"To make things simple and extendable (- which means in case of more integration of tools we should be able to accomblish it without changing, many lines of code -), I will generate a main Client struct which will have exec function and it will be overridden according to command we pass.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[{"__typename":"Markup","type":"CODE","start":188,"end":194,"href":null,"anchorType":null,"userId":null,"linkMetadata":null},{"__typename":"Markup","type":"CODE","start":218,"end":222,"href":null,"anchorType":null,"userId":null,"linkMetadata":null},{"__typename":"Markup","type":"A","start":247,"end":257,"href":"https:\u002F\u002Fen.wikipedia.org\u002Fwiki\u002FMethod_overriding","anchorType":"LINK","userId":null,"linkMetadata":null}],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:8d7b84ec45f2_25":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"8d7b84ec45f2_25","name":"23a0","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"The main client struct :","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"MediaResource:eb6b9bc9b891cfd80f7afeee982b0b68":{"__typename":"MediaResource","id":"eb6b9bc9b891cfd80f7afeee982b0b68","iframeSrc":"","iframeHeight":0,"iframeWidth":0,"title":"client.go"},"Paragraph:8d7b84ec45f2_26":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"8d7b84ec45f2_26","name":"b649","type":"IFRAME","href":null,"layout":"INSET_CENTER","metadata":null,"text":"","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":{"__typename":"Iframe","mediaResource":{"__ref":"MediaResource:eb6b9bc9b891cfd80f7afeee982b0b68"}},"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:8d7b84ec45f2_27":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"8d7b84ec45f2_27","name":"6292","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Client struct has some fields which enables us to override whenever we want, the struct contains exec(cmd string, args ...string) ([]byte, error), shellPipe(stdin io.Reader, cmd string, args ...string) ([]byte, error), and shellExec(cmd string, args ...string) ([]byte, error) functions. It can be extended according to our requirements in the future. The explanations of the functions are given on top of functions inside the source code.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[{"__typename":"Markup","type":"CODE","start":97,"end":145,"href":null,"anchorType":null,"userId":null,"linkMetadata":null},{"__typename":"Markup","type":"CODE","start":147,"end":217,"href":null,"anchorType":null,"userId":null,"linkMetadata":null},{"__typename":"Markup","type":"CODE","start":223,"end":276,"href":null,"anchorType":null,"userId":null,"linkMetadata":null}],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:8d7b84ec45f2_28":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"8d7b84ec45f2_28","name":"9ca9","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"For the youtube-dl client, I implemented only a function (-the client functionalities are really easy to extend-), which downloads all videos on given playlist by using pre-existing command line tool youtube-dl.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"MediaResource:126d381eed1afcdab033989ba9f1f4b3":{"__typename":"MediaResource","id":"126d381eed1afcdab033989ba9f1f4b3","iframeSrc":"","iframeHeight":0,"iframeWidth":0,"title":"client-1.go"},"Paragraph:8d7b84ec45f2_29":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"8d7b84ec45f2_29","name":"d416","type":"IFRAME","href":null,"layout":"INSET_CENTER","metadata":null,"text":"","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":{"__typename":"Iframe","mediaResource":{"__ref":"MediaResource:126d381eed1afcdab033989ba9f1f4b3"}},"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:8d7b84ec45f2_30":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"8d7b84ec45f2_30","name":"ccbb","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"For any other additional tool to use, it is extremely practical to add, for tar tool I have implemented following for specific purpose ( -which is compressing downloaded videos in parallel- ).","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"MediaResource:4ef500890bdf382b6d0987f1732337fe":{"__typename":"MediaResource","id":"4ef500890bdf382b6d0987f1732337fe","iframeSrc":"","iframeHeight":0,"iframeWidth":0,"title":"compress-func.go"},"Paragraph:8d7b84ec45f2_31":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"8d7b84ec45f2_31","name":"58b9","type":"IFRAME","href":null,"layout":"INSET_CENTER","metadata":null,"text":"","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":{"__typename":"Iframe","mediaResource":{"__ref":"MediaResource:4ef500890bdf382b6d0987f1732337fe"}},"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:8d7b84ec45f2_32":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"8d7b84ec45f2_32","name":"94b4","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Now, it is clear that for the both statements in the requirements section has been done. However, I wanted to keep track of what I have downloaded and release, for this reason, I have created two different csv files. They are called playlist-list.csv and old-playlist-list.csv under resources\u002F directory in the repository, playlist-list.csv will include all list of playlist URLs with preferred folder name to download. Futhermore, as you can guess, old-playlist-list.csv will include all the playlists which are downloaded and released. Once the playlist is downloaded and released with Github actions playlist-list.csv will be wiped and all content will be appended into old-playlist-list.csv file.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[{"__typename":"Markup","type":"CODE","start":233,"end":250,"href":null,"anchorType":null,"userId":null,"linkMetadata":null},{"__typename":"Markup","type":"CODE","start":255,"end":276,"href":null,"anchorType":null,"userId":null,"linkMetadata":null},{"__typename":"Markup","type":"CODE","start":323,"end":340,"href":null,"anchorType":null,"userId":null,"linkMetadata":null},{"__typename":"Markup","type":"CODE","start":450,"end":471,"href":null,"anchorType":null,"userId":null,"linkMetadata":null},{"__typename":"Markup","type":"CODE","start":603,"end":620,"href":null,"anchorType":null,"userId":null,"linkMetadata":null},{"__typename":"Markup","type":"CODE","start":673,"end":694,"href":null,"ancho